blScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg034.perseus-grc1:1459b:37\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Po.\">Po.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1459b37</biblScope> </bibl>: also <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the anapaestic tetrameter</tr_>, called <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τὸ Ἀριστοφάνειον</foreign> (as in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Nu.\">Nu.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">957</biblScope> </bibl> sq.), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0081.tlg012:25\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.H.\">D.H.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Comp.\">Comp.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">25</biblScope> </bibl>; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τρίμετρος</foreign>. </sense> <sense n=\"2\" id=\"n103440.1\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">γωνίαι τ</foreign>. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">square</tr_>, i.e. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">right</tr_>, angles, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg1240.tlg001:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Callix.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2</biblScope> </bibl> (dub. l.).</sense> </entryFree>"}]}